obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (68381)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68381&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be cited as “The Oudh Estates’ Act, 1869,” and shall`
  line `extent only to the estates hereinafter referred to.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (68382)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Interpretation - clause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68382&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `clause.--- In this Act, unless there be something repugnant in the subject or`
  line context.----
  line
  line `"Transfer."-- "Transfer" means an alienation inter vivos ;`
  line
  line `"Will".---"Will" means the legal declaration of the intentions of the testator with respect to his`
  line `property affected by this Act, which he desires to be carried into effect after his death ;`
  line
  line `"Codicil".--- "Codicil" means an instrument made in relation to a Will, and explaining, altering, or`
  line `adding to its dispositions : It is considered as forming an additional part of the Will ;`
  line
  line `"Signed."--- "Signed" applies to the affixing of a mark ;`
  line
  line `"Registered".--- "Registered" means registered according to the provisions of the rules relating to the`
  line `registration of assurances for the time being in force in Oudh ;`
  line
  line `"Minor". "Minority".--- "Minor" means any person who shall not have completed the age of`
  line `eighteen years, and "minority" means the status of such person ;`
  line
  line `"Taluqdar".--- "Taluqdar" means any person whose name is entered in the first of the lists mentioned`
  line `in section eight ;`
  line
  line `"Grantee".--- "Grantee" means any person upon whom the proprietary right in an estate has been`
  line `conferred by a special grant of the British Government, and whose name is entered in the fifth or sixth of`
  line `the lists mentioned in section eight ;`
  line
  line `"Estate" .--- "Estate" means the taluqa or immoveable property acquired or held by a Taluqdar or`
  line `Grantee in the manner mentioned in section three, section four, or section five, or the immoveable`
  line `property conferred by a special grant of the British Government upon a Grantee ;`
  line
  line `"Heir" "Legatee" .--- "Heir"means a person who inherits property otherwise than as a widow, under`
  line `the special provisions of this Act ; and "legatee" means a person to whom property is bequeathed under`
  line `the same provisions ;`
  line
  line `Words expressing relationship .--- Words expressing relationship denote only legitimate relatives,`
  line `but apply to children in the womb who are afterwards born alive.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (68384)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Taluqdars to have heritable and transferable rights in their estates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68384&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Every Taluqdar with`
  line `whom a summary settlement of the Government revenue was made between the first day of April 1858`
  line `and the tenth day of October 1859, or to whom, before the passing of this Act and subsequently to the`
  line `first day of April 1858, a Taluqdari sanad has been granted,`
  line
  line `Shall be deemed to have thereby acquired a permanent, heritable and transferable right in the estate`
  line `comprising the villages and lands named in the list attached to the agreement or kabuliyat executed by`
  line `such Taluqdar when such settlement was made,`
  line
  line `or which may have been or may be decreed to him by the Court of an officer engaged in making the`
  line `first regular settlement of the provinces of Oudh, such decree not having been appealed from within the`
  line `time limited for appealing against it, or, if appealed from, having been affirmed,`
  line
  line `Subject to certain conditions. ---Subject to all the conditions affecting the Taluqdar contained in the`
  line `orders passed by the Governor General of India on the tenth and nineteenth days of October 1859 and republished in the first schedule hereto annexed, and subject also to all the conditions contained in the`
  line `sanad under which the estate is held.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (68385)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Rights and liabilities of persons named in second schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68385&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Every person whose lands the`
  line `proclamation issued in Oudh in the month of March 1858 by order of the Governor General of India`
  line `specially exempted from confiscation, and whose names are contained in the second schedule hereto`
  line `annexed, shall be deemed to possess in the lands for which such person executed a kabuliyat between the`
  line `first day of April 1858 and the first day of April 1860 the same right and title which he would have`
  line `possessed thereto if he had acquired the same in the manner mentioned in section three ; and he shall be`
  line `deemed to hold the same subject to all the conditions affecting Taluqdárs which are referred to in the said`
  line `section, and to be a Taluqdár for all the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (68386)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Grantees' rights and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68386&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every Grantee shall possess the same rights and be subject to`
  line `the same conditions in respect of the estate comprised in his grant as a Taluqdár possesses and is subject`
  line `to, under section three, in respect of his estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (68387)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Saving of certain redemption-suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68387&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in sections three, four and five, or in the said`
  line `orders, or in any sanad, shall be deemed to bar a suit for redemption,`
  line
  line `(a) where the instrument of mortgage was executed on or after the thirteenth day of February 1844 and`
  line `fixed no term within which the property comprised therein might be redeemed, or`
  line
  line `(b) where the instrument of mortgage fixed a term within which the property comprised therein might`
  line `be redeemed, and such term did not expire before the thirteenth day of February 1856.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (68388)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Heirlooms.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68388&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If a Taluqdár or Grantee, or any heir or legatee of a Taluqdár or Grantee, desire that`
  line `any elephants, jewels, arms or other articles of moveable property belonging to him shall devolve song`
  line `with his estate, he shall take an inventory of such articles. Such inventory shall be signed by him and deposited in the office of the Deputy Commissioner of the District wherein such estate or the greater part`
  line `thereof is situate ; and thereupon such of the said articles as shall not have been transferred shall (so far as`
  line `may be possible) be used and enjoyed by the person who, under or by virtue of this Act, is for the time`
  line `being in actual possession or in receipt of the rents and profits of the said estate or the greater part`
  line `thereof, otherwise than as mortgagee or lessee.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (68390)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Preparation of lists of Taluqdars and Grantees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68390&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Within six months after the passing of this Act,`
  line `the Chief Commissioner of Oudh, subject to such instructions as he may receive from the Governor`
  line `General of India in Council, shall cause to be prepared six lists, namely :—`
  line
  line `First.— A list of all persons who are to be considered Taluqdárs within the meaning of this Act ;`
  line
  line `Second.— A list of the Taluqdárs whose estates, according to the custom of the family on and before`
  line `the thirteenth day of February 1856, ordinarily devolved upon a single heir ;`
  line
  line `Third.— A list of the Taluqdárs, not included in the second of such lists, to whom sanads or grants`
  line `have been or may be given or made by the British Government up to the date fixed for the closing of such`
  line `lists, declaring that the succession to the estates comprised in such sanads or grants shall thereafter be`
  line `regulated by the rule of primogeniture;`
  line
  line `Fourth.— A list of the Taluqdárs to whom the provisions of section twenty-three are applicable ;`
  line
  line `Fifth.— A list of the Grantees to whom sanads or grants have been or may be given or made by the`
  line `British Government, up to the date for the closing of such list, declaring that the succession to the estates`
  line `comprised in such sanads or grants shall thereafter be regulated by the rule of primogeniture ;`
  line
  line `Sixth.— A list of the Grantees to whom the provisions of section twenty-three are applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (68391)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Publication of lists.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68391&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `When the lists mentioned in section eight shall have been approved by the`
  line `Chief Commissioner of Oudh, they shall be published in the Gazette of India After such publication, the`
  line `first and second of the said lists not, except in the manner provided by section thirty or section thirty-one,`
  line `as the case may be, be liable to any alteration in respect of any names entered therein.`
  line
  line `Supplementary list.— If, at any time after the publication of the said lists, it appears to the Governor`
  line `General of India in Council that the name of any person has been wrongly omitted from or wrongly`
  line `entered in any of the said lists, the said Governor General in Council may order the name to be inserted in`
  line `the proper list, and such name shall be published in the Gazette of India in a supplementary list, and such`
  line `person shall be treated in all respects as if his name had been from the first inserted in the proper list.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (68392)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `None but persons named in lists to be deemed Taluqdars or Grantees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68392&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No persons shall be`
  line `considered Taluqd'ars or Grantees within the meaning of this Act, other than the persons named in such`
  line `original or supplementary lists as aforesaid. The Courts shall take judicial notice of the said lists and shall`
  line `regard them as conclusive evidence that the persons named therein are such Taluqd'ars or Grantees.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (68394)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Taluqdars and Grantees may transfer and bequeath.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68394&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the Provisions of this Act,`
  line `and to all the conditions under which the estate was conferred by the British Government, every Taluqdar`
  line `and Grantee, and every heir and legatee of a Taluqdar and Grantee, of sound mind and not a minor, shall`
  line `be competent to transfer the whole or any portion of his estate, or of his right and interest therein, during his life-time, by sale, exchange, mortgage, lease or gift, and to bequeath by his will to any person the`
  line `whole or any portion of such estate, right and interest.`
  line
  line `A married woman may make a bequest under this Act of any property which she could alienate by her`
  line `own act during her life.`
  line
  line `Persons who are deaf or dumb or blind are not thereby incapacitated for making a transfer or bequest`
  line `under this Act, if they are able to know what they do by it.`
  line
  line `One who is ordinarily insane may make a transfer or bequest under this Act during an interval in`
  line `which he is of sound mind.`
  line
  line `No person can make a transfer or bequest under this Act while he is in such a state of mind, whether`
  line `from drunkenness, or from illness, or from any other cause, that he does not know what he is doing.`
  line
  line `A transfer and a will, or any part of a will, the making of which has been caused by fraud or coercion`
  line `or by such importunity as takes away the free agency of the transferor or testator, is void.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (68395)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Rule against perpetuity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68395&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No transfer or bequest under this Act shall be valid whereby`
  line `the vesting of the thing transferred or bequeathed may be delayed beyond the life-time of one or`
  line `more persons living at the decease of the transferee or testator and the minority of some person`
  line `who shall be in existence at the expiration of that period, and to whom, if he attains full age, the`
  line `thing transferred or bequeathed is to belong.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (68396)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Restriction as to donees and legatees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68396&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No Taluqdár or Grantee, and no heir or legatee of a`
  line `Taluqdár or Grantee, shall have power to give or bequeath his estate, or any portion thereof, or any`
  line `interest therein, to any person not being either-`
  line
  line `(1.) —a person who, under the provision of this Act, or under the ordinary law to which person of`
  line `the donor's or testator's tribe and religion are subject, would have succeeded to such estate or to a`
  line `portion thereof, or to an interest therein, if such Taluqdár or Grantee, heir or legatee, had died`
  line `intestate, or`
  line
  line `(2.) — a younger son of the Taluqdár or Grantee, heir or legatee, in case the name of such Taluqdár`
  line `or Grantee appears in the third or the fifth of the lists mentioned in section eight, except by an`
  line `instrument of gift or a will executed and attested, not less than three months before the death of the`
  line `donor or testator, in manner herein provided in the case of a gift or will, as the case may be, and`
  line `registered within one month from the date of its execution.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (68398)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Transfers and bequests to Taluqdars or heirs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68398&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If any Taluqdár or Grantee shall theretofore`
  line `have transferred or bequeathed, or if any Taluqdár or Grantee, or his heir or legatee, shall`
  line `hereafter transfer or bequeath, the whole or any portion of his estate to another Taluqdár or`
  line `Grantee, or to such younger son as is referred to in section thirteen, clause two, or to a person`
  line `who would have succeeded according to the provisions of this Act to the estate or to a portion`
  line `thereof if the transferor or testator had died without having made the transfer and intestate, the`
  line `transferee or legatee and his heirs and legatees shall have the same rights and powers in regard to`
  line `the property to which he or they may have become entitled under or by virtue of such t ransfer or`
  line `bequest, and shall hold the same subject to the same conditions and to the same rules of`
  line `succession as the transferor or testator.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (68399)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Transfers and bequests to persons out of line of seccession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68399&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If any Taluqdár or Grantee`
  line `shall heretofore have transferred or bequeathed, or if any Taluqdár or Grantee or his heir or`
  line `legatee shall hereafter transfer or bequeath to any person not being a Taluqdár or Grantee the`
  line `whole or any portion of his estate, and such person would not have succeeded according to the`
  line `provisions of this Act to the estate or to a portion thereof if the transferor or testator had died`
  line `without having made the transfer and intestate, the transfer of and succession to the property so`
  line `transferred or bequeathed shall be regulated by the rules which would have governed the transfer`
  line `of and succession to such property if the transferee or legatee had bought the same from a person`
  line `not being a Taluqdár or Grantee.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (68400)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Transfers to be in writing, signed and attested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68400&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No transfer of any estate, or of any`
  line `portion thereof, or of any interest therein, made by a Taluqdár or Grantee or by his heir or`
  line `legatee under the provisions of this Act, shall be valid unless made by an instrument in writing`
  line `signed by the transferor and attested by two or more witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (68401)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Further requisites to validity of gifts inter vivos.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68401&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `If any such transfer be made by gift, the`
  line `gift shall not be valid unless, within six months after the execution of the instrument of gift, the gift`
  line `be followed by delivery by the donor, or his representative in interest, of possession of the property`
  line `comprised therein, nor unless the instrument shall have been registered within one month from the`
  line `date of its execution.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (68402)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Gifts to religious or charitable uses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68402&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No Taluqdár or Grantee, and no heir or legatee of a`
  line `Taluqdár or Grantee, shall have power to give his estate, or any portion thereof or interest therein, to`
  line `religious or charitable uses, except by an instrument of gift executed not less than three months`
  line `before his death, and subject to the provisions contained in section seventeen.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (68404)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Sections of Succession Act applied to wills of Taluqdars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68404&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Sections 49, 50, 51, 54, 55,`
  line `and 57 to 77 (both inclusive), and sections 82, 83, 85, and 88 to 98 (both inclusive) of the Indian`
  line `Succession Act (No. X of 1865), shall apply to all wills and codicils made by any Taluqd�r or`
  line `Grantee, or by his heir or legatee, under the provisions of this Act, for the purpose of bequeathing to`
  line `any person his estate, or any portion thereof, or any interest therein: Provided that marriage shall not`
  line `revoke any such will or codicil :`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing herein contained shall affect wills made`
  line `before the passing of this Act.`
  line
  line `In applying the said sections to wills and codicils made under this Act, all words hereinbefore`
  line `defined, and occurring in such sections, shall (unless there be something repugnant in the subject or`
  line `context) be deemed to have the same meaning as this Act has attached to such words respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (68405)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Bequests to religious and charitable uses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68405&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `No Taluqdár or Grantee and no heir or`
  line `legatee of a Taluqdár or Grantee, having Child, parent, brother, unmarried sister, or a nephew, being`
  line `the naturally born son of a brother of such Taluqdár or Grantee, heir or legatee, shall have power to`
  line `bequeath his estate or any part thereof or any interest therein exceeding in amount or value the sum`
  line `of two thousand rupees to religious or charitable uses, except by a will executed not less than three`
  line `months before his death, and registered within one month from the date of its execution.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (68407)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `'Son,' 'descendants,' 'daughter,' 'brother,' 'widow,' defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68407&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `In the next following`
  line `section, unless where there is something repugnant in the context, the words ‘son,’ ‘descendants,’`
  line `‘daughter’ and ‘brother’ apply only to najib-ul-tarfain, and the word ‘widow’ applies only to a`
  line `woman belonging to the ahl-i-bradari of her deceased husband.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (68408)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Special rules of succession to intestate Taluqdars and Grantees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68408&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `If any Taluqdar or`
  line `Grantee whose name shall be inserted in the second, third, or fifth of the lists mentioned in`
  line `section eight, or his heir or legatee, shall die intestate as to his estate, such estate shall descend as`
  line `follows: viz :--`
  line
  line `(l).--To the eldest son of such Taluqdar or Grantee, heir or legatee, and his male lineal`
  line `descendants, subject to the same conditions and in the same manner as the estate was held by`
  line `the deceased;`
  line
  line `(2).--Or if such eldest son of such Taluqdar or Grantee, heir or legatee, shall have died in`
  line `his life-time, leaving male lineal descendants, then to the eldest and every other son of such`
  line `eldest son successively, according to their respective seniorities, and their respective male`
  line `lineal descendants, subject as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(3).--Or if such eldest son of such Taluqdar or Grantee, heir or legatee, shall have died in`
  line `his life-time without leaving male lineal descendants, then to the second and every other on of`
  line `the aid Taluqdr or Grantee, heir or legatee, successively, according to their respective`
  line `seniorities, and their respective male lineal descendants, subject as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(4).--Or in default of such son or descendants, then to such son (if any) of a daughter of`
  line `such Taluqdar or Grantee, heir or legatee, as has been treated by him in all respects as his own`
  line `son, and to the male lineal descendants of such son, subject as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(5).--Or in default of such son or descendants, then to such person as the said Taluqdar or`
  line `Grantee, heir or legatee, shall have adopted by a writing executed and attested in manner`
  line `required in case of a will and registered, subject as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(6).---Or in default of such adopted son, then to the eldest and every other brother of such`
  line `Taluqdar or Grantee, heir or legatee, successively, according to their respective seniorities,`
  line `and their respective male lineal descendants, subject as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(7).--Or in default of any such brother, then to the widow of the deceased Taluqdr or`
  line `Grantee, heir or legatee; or, if there be more widows than one, to t he widow first married to`
  line `such Taluqdar or Grantee, heir or legatee, for her life-time only;`
  line
  line `(8).--And upon the death of such widow, then to such son as the said widow shall, with`
  line `the consent in writing of her deceased husband, have adopted by a writing executed and`
  line `attested in manner required in case of a will and registered, subject as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(9).--Or on the death of such first married widow and in default of a son adopted by her`
  line `with such consent and in such manner as aforesaid, then to the other widow, if any, of such`
  line `Taluqdar or Grantee, heir or legatee, next in order of marriage, for her life, and on the death of`
  line `such other widow, to a son adopted by her with such consent and in such manner as aforesaid;`
  line `or in default of such adopted son, then to the other surviving widows according to their`
  line `respective seniorities as widows, for their respective lives, and on their respective deaths, to`
  line `the sons so adopted by them respectively, and to the male lineal descendants of such sons`
  line `respectively, subject as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(10).--Or in default of any such widow or of any son so adopted by her; or of any such`
  line `descendant, then to the male lineal descendants, not being najib-ul-tarfain, of such Taluqdar or`
  line `Grantee, heir or legatee, successively, according to their respective seniorities and their`
  line `respective male lineal descendant, whether najib-ul-tarfain or not;`
  line
  line `(11).--Or in default of any such descendant, then to such persons as would have been entitled to`
  line `succeed to the estate under the ordinary law to which persons of the religion and tribe of such Taluqdar`
  line `or Grantee, heir or legatee, are subject.`
  line
  line `Nothing contained in the former part of this section shall be construed to limit the power of`
  line `alienation conferred by section eleven.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (68409)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `General rule of succession to intestate Taluqdars and Grantees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68409&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Except in the cases provided`
  line `for by section twenty-two, the succession to all property left by Taluqdárs and Grantees, and their heirs`
  line `and legatees, dying intestate, shall be regulated by the ordinary law to which members of the intestate's`
  line `tribe and religion are subject.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (68411)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Maintenance of surviving relatives of Taluqdars and Grantees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68411&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `When any Taluqdár or`
  line `Grantee, or his heir or legatee, dies leaving him surviving such relatives as are hereinafter mentioned, the`
  line `person for the time being in the possession of his estate or the rents and profits thereof shall be liable to pay to each of such relatives during his or her life, or for such other period as is hereinafter mentioned, by`
  line `twelve equal monthly payments, an annuity in accordance with the custom of the country not exceeding`
  line `such amount as is hereinafter mentioned : Provided that such relative was at the date of the death of the`
  line `deceased living together with him: Provided also that such relative is and continues to be without any`
  line `other adequate means of maintenance.`
  line
  line `If any part of such estate shall have been transferred or bequeathed by the deceased, that person for the`
  line `time being in possession of such part, or of the rent and profits thereof, shall be liable to pay proportionate`
  line `parts of the said annuities the continuance thereof respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (68412)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Grandparents, parents, and senior widows. Junior widows.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68412&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `In the case of the grandparents, parents, and`
  line `senior widows of the deceased, the maximum amount of the annuity shall be as follows :---`
  line
  line `(a.) where the annual revenue payable to Government in respect of the estate is or exceeds 1,50,000`
  line `rupees⸻⸻a sum not exceeding 6,000 rupees :`
  line
  line `(b.) where such revenue is or exceeds 100,000 rupees, but is less than 1,50,000 rupees a sum`
  line `not exceeding 2,400 rupees :`
  line
  line `(c.) where such revenue is or exceeds 50,000 rupees, but is less than 100,000 rupees ⸻⸻ a sum`
  line `not exceeding 1,200 rupees :`
  line
  line `(d.) where such revenue is or exceeds 25,000 rupees, but is less than 50,000 rupees ⸻⸻ a sum not`
  line `exceeding 600 rupees :`
  line
  line `(e.) where such revenue is or exceeds 15,000 rupees, but is less than 25,000 rupees ⸻⸻ a sum not`
  line `exceeding 360 rupees :`
  line
  line `(f.) where such revenue is or exceeds 7,000 rupees, but is less than 15,000 rupees ⸻⸻ a sum not`
  line `exceeding 240 rupees ; and`
  line
  line `(g.) where such revenue is less than 7,000 rupees⸻ a sum not exceeding 180 rupees.`
  line
  line `Junior widows.— In the case of a junior widow of the deceased, the maximum amount of the`
  line `annuity shall be one-half of the maximum amount to which a senior widow of the deceased would be`
  line `entitled under the former part of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (68413)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Brothers and minor sons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68413&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `In the case of brothers and minor sons of the deceased, the`
  line `maximum amount of the annuity shall be a sum not more than 1,200 rupees.`
  line
  line `Nephews.— In the case of nephews of the deceased, being father less minors, the maximum`
  line `amount of the annuity shall be a sum not more than 600 rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (68414)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Unmarried daughters, widows of sons and brothers and inferior widows.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68414&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `In the case of`
  line `unmarried daughters of the deceased, widows of his sons and brothers, and his widows not of his ahli·bradari, the maximum amount of the annuity shall be a sum not more than 360 rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (68415)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Continuance of annuities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68415&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions hereinbefore contained, the aid`
  line `annuities hall continue,`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a minor son or a minor nephew, till he ceases to be a minor;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a daughter or widow, till she voluntarily leaves the household of the heir or`
  line `legatee of the deceased, or would, according to the custom of the country, cease to be entitled to`
  line `maintenance, and`
  line
  line `(c) in all other cases, till the annuitant dies.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (68417)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Muhammadan Taluqdars and Grantees empowered to adopt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68417&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Every Muhammadan`
  line `Taluqdár, Grantee, heir or legatee, and every widow of a Muhammadan Taluqdár or Grantee, heir or`
  line `legatee, with the consent in writing of her deceased husband, shall, for the purposes of this Act, have`
  line `power to adopt a son whenever, if he or she were a Hind, he or she might adopt a son.`
  line
  line `Such, power shall be exercisable only by writing executed and attested in manner required by section`
  line `nineteen in case of a will and registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (68422)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Alteration of rules of intestate succession in cases of Taluqdárs and Grantees named in list 3 or list 5.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68422&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Any Taluqdár or Grantee whose name has been entered in the third or fifth of the lists`
  line `mentioned in section eight, or his heir or legatee, may, at any time hereafter, present to the Chief`
  line `Commissioner of Oudh a declaration in writing, executed and registered in the manner required by this`
  line `Act for the execution and registration of an instrument of gift, that he is desirous that the succession to his`
  line `estate shall, in case of his intestacy, cease to be regulated in the manner described in section twenty-two,`
  line `and that it shall in future be regulated by the ordinary law to which members of his tribe and religion are`
  line subject.
  line
  line `On receiving such declaration, the said Chief Commissioner shall cause to be inserted the name of`
  line `such Taluqdár or Grantee, heir or legatee, in the fourth or sixth (as the case may be) of the lists mentioned`
  line `in section eight, and shall cause a note thereof to be made in the proper place in the third or fifth (as the`
  line `case may be) of the said lists, and the succession to such estate shall thenceforward, in case of intestacy,`
  line `be regulated in the manner provided by section twenty-three.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (68419)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Reverter to ordinary law of succession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68419&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any Taluqdár or Grantee, heir or legatee, may, at any`
  line `time hereafter, present to the Chief Commissioner of Oudh a declaration in writing, executed and`
  line `registered in the manner required by this Act for the execution and registration of instruments of gift, that`
  line `he is desirous that his estate should in future be held subject to the ordinary law of succession to which`
  line `members of his tribe and religion are subject.`
  line
  line `On receiving such declaration, the Chief Commissioner shall cause a note thereof to be made in the`
  line `proper places in each of the lists mentioned in section eight in which the name of such Taluqdár or`
  line `Grantee, heir or legatee, has been entered, and thenceforward none of the provisions of this Act shall`
  line `apply to such estate, which shall thenceforward be held subject in all respects to the ordinary law of`
  line `succession to which members of his tribe and religion are subject.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (68420)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Saving of rights of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68420&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Nothing hereinbefore contained shall affect any right which the`
  line `creditors of any person making a transfer or bequest under the provisions of this Act, would have`
  line `possessed as against the property comprised in such transfer or bequest if this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (68421)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Awards as to compensation and maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032&sectionId=68421&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00102_186901_1663845682032
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `And whereas bodies of Taluqdárs have in`
  line `several cases made awards respecting the provision to be made for certain relatives of Taluqdárs, and it is`
  line `expedient to render such awards legally enforceable; it is hereby further enacted that every such award`
  line `shall, if approved by the financial Commissioner of Oudh and filed in his Court within six months after`
  line `the passing of this Act, he enforceable as if a Court of competent jurisdiction had passed judgment`
  line `according to the award and a decree had followed upon such judgment.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
